      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Guide",
      "description": "Use this folder first. It explains the current auth split and the expected request order for working with the backend from Postman.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Guide - Collection Overview",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "description": "Overview for this collection.\n\nUse cases covered now:\n- Health check the backend\n- Register with OTP-based email verification\n- Verify email with OTP\n- Sign in through Better Auth session endpoints for protected business routes\n- Optionally use legacy compatibility login routes under /api/v1/auth\n- Fetch and update the authenticated user profile\n- List or manage course categories\n- Browse public courses\n- Create, edit, delete, and submit instructor courses\n\nRecommended request order for protected course-platform APIs:\n1. Run Health\n2. Run Auth - Register\n3. Run Auth - Verify Email\n4. Run Auth - Better Auth Sign In\n5. Run Auth - Better Auth Get Session\n6. Run Users -> Get My Profile\n7. Continue with Categories or Courses\n\nModule map:\n- Health: readiness endpoint\n- Auth: OTP signup verification, Better Auth session endpoints, and compatibility auth routes\n- Users: profile and learning summary\n- Course Categories: public taxonomy plus admin category management\n- Courses: public discovery and instructor draft management\n\nFuture use cases that will be added into this same collection:\n- Student checkout and enrollment\n- Lesson playback and progress tracking\n- Reviews and ratings\n- Admin moderation and reporting",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Guide - Auth And Session Usage",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "description": "Current auth behavior in Postman.\n\nImportant behavior:\n- Signup verification uses OTP routes under /api/v1/auth/*.\n- Protected business routes under /api/v1/users, /api/v1/categories/admin, and instructor course routes use the Better Auth session resolved by authorize() middleware.\n- That means the recommended login route for protected business APIs is /api/auth/sign-in/email, not /api/v1/auth/login.\n- The /api/v1/auth/login, /refresh, and /logout routes still exist, but they issue custom auth cookies and are not the primary session mechanism for course-platform endpoints.\n\nRecommended auth flow:\n1. Auth - Register\n2. Auth - Verify Email\n3. Auth - Better Auth Sign In\n4. Auth - Better Auth Get Session\n5. Protected business requests\n\nIf OTP expires:\n- use Auth - Resend Verification OTP\n\nIf Better Auth cookies are not being reused:\n- inspect Postman Cookies for {{baseUrl}}",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
